# Week 3 - MQTT Pipline
### This project serves as a specialized security laboratory designed to model common vulnerabilities inherent in unhardened Internet of Things (IoT) infrastructure. 
The architecture facilitates the ingestion of device telemetry in cleartext, providing a practical testbed for analyzing protocol behavior and identifying potential exploit vectors within local network communication.
By engineering an MQTT pipeline without Transport Layer Security (TLS) or authentication, I established a controlled environment to simulate insecure data transmission. 
